  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-03-31",
    "date": "2022-05-17T20:22:09Z",
    "text": "Stablecoin Transparency Act \n\nThis bill requires a stablecoin issuer to hold all reserves associated with each fiat currency-backed stablecoin they issue in (1) certain government securities; (2) fully collateralized security repurchase agreements, and (3) U.S. dollars or other nondigital currency. A fiat currency-backed stablecoin is a digital asset backed by a nondigital currency and is redeemable on a one-to-one basis in that currency.\n\nEach stablecoin issuer must publish monthly on their website a report on the reserves held by the issuer that has been audited by a third party."
  },
